                                                                            <comments>
                            <comment id="232781" author="jgmitter" created="Thu, 30 Aug 2018 02:44:14 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;It appears that the version is buried too deep from the top of the document due to how the Docbook processing works. &#160;By default, it always renders the copyright info first and then the version info second. &#160;Our copyright is huge and my blind guess is that it was just easier to accept the default than to figure out how to get Docbook to print out the version before the copyright. &#160;The result is a separate section after the copyright to print out the version.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;I&apos;ll do some experimentation to see if I can get it to do that.&#160;&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
